README for jaxdoc - the javascript enhanced rdoc template

The files included in this first release allow you to create a javascript enhanced rdoc (similar to what is on www.railsbrain.com right now).

To use these files you'll need to copy them to the rdoc folder in the directory for your local ruby install.

git clone git://github.com/tiendung/ajax-rdoc.git

sudo cp ajax-rdoc/rdoc/generators/ajax_generator.rb /usr/local/lib/ruby/1.8/rdoc/generators

sudo cp -R ajax-rdoc/rdoc/generators/template/ajax /usr/local/lib/ruby/1.8/rdoc/generators/template

Switch over to the directory where you want to run this rdoc template
rdoc --fmt ajax

NOTE: The title is set to the dir name that running rdoc command.

Some shortcuts

alias jaxdoc="rdoc --fmt ajax --exclude .*generator.* --exclude .*test.* --exclude .*spec.*"

alias railsdoc="cd ~/src/rails && jaxdoc --op ~/doc/rails actionmailer activerecord actionpack activemodel activesupport activeresource railties"


